1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,586
[Espina] <i>In my dream, I had a brother.</i>

2
00:00:03,670 --> 00:00:05,088
<i>He was the one saving me.</i>

3
00:00:05,171 --> 00:00:06,840
I want to know the truth.

4
00:00:06,923 --> 00:00:09,718
[Omar] <i>How long are you planning</i>
<i>to hide your secret, Rahman?</i>

5
00:00:09,801 --> 00:00:10,927
Especially from Jalil.

6
00:00:11,010 --> 00:00:13,346
I called so you'd stop worrying.

7
00:00:13,430 --> 00:00:15,557
You have to be more careful.

8
00:00:15,640 --> 00:00:18,184
We're close to solving the case.

9
00:00:18,268 --> 00:00:22,522
[Datu Rahman] <i>The next time we meet,</i>
<i>I will tell you something.</i>

10
00:00:23,148 --> 00:00:24,441
[Eve, in English]
<i>We're under a lot of fire.</i>

11
00:00:24,524 --> 00:00:27,277
No wonder people
are criticizing and attacking us.

12
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:29,696
[Ryan] <i>All right, sir.</i>
<i>We're only missing Agent Angeles now.</i>

13
00:00:29,779 --> 00:00:30,697
Where is she?

14
00:00:30,780 --> 00:00:31,906
She hasn't shown herself

15
00:00:31,990 --> 00:00:34,159
ever since the explosion
at San Aurelio Street.

16
00:00:34,242 --> 00:00:36,536
[Espina] <i>Even our other members</i>
<i>were puzzled.</i>

17
00:00:36,619 --> 00:00:39,164
[Marcus] <i>You know, there are only</i>
<i>two possible reasons.</i>

18
00:00:39,247 --> 00:00:41,291
[Marcus] It's either her life
is in danger right now

19
00:00:41,374 --> 00:00:44,919
or she blew the bus up herself,
and now she's hiding.

20
00:00:45,003 --> 00:00:47,005
I still hope that she's safe.

21
00:00:47,088 --> 00:00:50,008
I genuinely trusted her
because we both lost someone.

22
00:00:50,091 --> 00:00:51,176
Lost someone?

23
00:00:51,259 --> 00:00:53,636
[Marcus] <i>Both of Lara's parents</i>
<i>were doctors.</i>

24
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:55,638
<i>They both died</i>

25
00:00:55,722 --> 00:00:59,017
<i>in an ambush during</i>
<i>a medical mission they were on.</i>

26
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:00,685
<i>Lara became an orphan at a young age.</i>

27
00:01:00,769 --> 00:01:03,104
<i>That's why General Carillo took her in.</i>

28
00:01:04,481 --> 00:01:07,108
[Jalil] <i>Are you General Carillo's</i>
<i>accomplice, Lara?</i>

29
00:01:08,318 --> 00:01:11,738
<i>Or is he trying to silence you,</i>
<i>just like his other victims?</i>

30
00:01:11,821 --> 00:01:13,406
[Manuel] <i>Were you able to contact Lara?</i>

31
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:15,283
Not yet, General.

32
00:01:16,367 --> 00:01:17,786
[Felix] <i>Lara!</i>

33
00:01:18,286 --> 00:01:19,412
<i>Where are you?</i>

34
00:01:19,496 --> 00:01:21,623
- [voice prompt] <i>The subscriber cannot be…</i>
- <i>Pick up.</i>

35
00:01:21,706 --> 00:01:25,502
[tense music playing]

36
00:01:29,464 --> 00:01:33,635
[mysterious theme music playing]

37
00:01:51,611 --> 00:01:55,907
[morose music playing]

38
00:02:00,995 --> 00:02:03,081
[doorbell rings]

39
00:02:06,876 --> 00:02:08,169
[doorbell rings]

40
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:12,841
[doorbell rings]

41
00:02:27,230 --> 00:02:32,485
[music turns unsettling]

42
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:38,700
[lock rattling]

43
00:02:39,534 --> 00:02:40,535
[lock rattling]

44
00:02:41,161 --> 00:02:43,413
[door squeaks open]

45
00:02:49,711 --> 00:02:50,628
Lara.

46
00:02:54,007 --> 00:02:56,092
[door squeaking]

47
00:02:57,927 --> 00:02:58,887
Lara?

48
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:05,393
Lara?

49
00:03:09,689 --> 00:03:10,648
Lara?

50
00:03:12,901 --> 00:03:13,776
Lara?

51
00:03:14,777 --> 00:03:15,862
Madam!

52
00:03:24,454 --> 00:03:25,496
Madam!

53
00:03:32,295 --> 00:03:33,254
Lara?

54
00:03:38,176 --> 00:03:41,471
[music turns tense]

55
00:03:41,554 --> 00:03:42,764
Lara!

56
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:48,019
[door thuds]

57
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:51,231
Where are you, Lara?

58
00:03:51,981 --> 00:03:54,692
[Lara sobbing]

59
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:59,197
[Lara sobbing]

60
00:04:01,532 --> 00:04:04,744
[Lara sobbing]

61
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:09,999
[morose music playing]

62
00:04:14,212 --> 00:04:15,546
[breathes deeply]

63
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:19,509
[tense music playing]

64
00:04:20,009 --> 00:04:21,052
[exhales sharply]

65
00:04:27,725 --> 00:04:30,603
Now that the alleged terrorists are dead,

66
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:33,064
<i>has the case truly been closed,</i>

67
00:04:33,147 --> 00:04:35,733
<i>or has the truth simply</i>
<i>been buried along with them?</i>

68
00:04:35,817 --> 00:04:38,444
In an interview with Agent Marcus Reyes,

69
00:04:38,528 --> 00:04:41,406
this is what he had to say.

70
00:04:41,489 --> 00:04:43,950
We're still looking into everything.

71
00:04:44,033 --> 00:04:50,039
The suspects, their motive,
and where they got their weapons.

72
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:52,458
But all I can say is this.

73
00:04:52,542 --> 00:04:54,836
This wasn't some simple act of violence.

74
00:04:56,129 --> 00:04:58,464
There's a deeper reason
behind what they did…

75
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:03,011
and someone powerful pushed them to do it.

76
00:05:03,928 --> 00:05:07,348
[Maya Mae] <i>While we mourn</i>
<i>the senseless loss of so many lives,</i>

77
00:05:07,432 --> 00:05:11,728
<i>we must remember that this incident</i>
<i>has resulted in many casualties.</i>

78
00:05:12,312 --> 00:05:14,939
The economy, people's livelihoods,

79
00:05:15,023 --> 00:05:17,734
and our diplomatic relations
with other countries.

80
00:05:19,235 --> 00:05:20,194
[in English] <i>No!</i>

81
00:05:20,862 --> 00:05:22,822
[in English] <i>They killed my family!</i>

82
00:05:22,905 --> 00:05:25,366
[pensive music playing]

83
00:05:25,450 --> 00:05:29,662
[in English] I will see to it that…
[sniffles]

84
00:05:29,746 --> 00:05:32,749
the investment deals don't push through!

85
00:05:37,128 --> 00:05:38,671
[in English] I will never…

86
00:05:39,630 --> 00:05:44,177
[in English] I will never set foot
in this country again!

87
00:05:45,219 --> 00:05:49,599
Miss Suher, I miss Mama and Papa so much.

88
00:05:49,682 --> 00:05:51,684
[sobbing]

89
00:05:52,310 --> 00:05:55,772
[Maya Mae] <i>As the number</i>
<i>of victims and grieving families</i>

90
00:05:55,855 --> 00:05:58,441
<i>affected by violence caused</i>
<i>by illegal firearms</i>

91
00:05:58,524 --> 00:06:01,736
<i>continues to grow, so do the questions.</i>

92
00:06:01,819 --> 00:06:04,322
How did a simple driver and tour guide

93
00:06:04,405 --> 00:06:08,076
get their hands on high-powered guns
for a hostage-taking?

94
00:06:08,159 --> 00:06:12,663
[Maya Mae] <i>Why would they blow up a bus</i>
<i>with themselves inside</i>

95
00:06:12,747 --> 00:06:16,250
<i>when they knew they had a child</i>
<i>waiting for them at home?</i>

96
00:06:16,334 --> 00:06:20,671
<i>Why does it feel like</i>
<i>the government isn't doing enough?</i>

97
00:06:20,755 --> 00:06:22,465
[in English] <i>Who will take accountability?</i>

98
00:06:22,548 --> 00:06:24,717
<i>And when will all of this finally end?</i>

99
00:06:25,301 --> 00:06:29,138
Hopefully, these questions
will be answered in our next episode,

100
00:06:29,222 --> 00:06:32,725
featuring an exclusive and live
face-to-face discussion between

101
00:06:32,809 --> 00:06:36,062
Presidential Chief of Staff Ahmad Mustapha

102
00:06:36,145 --> 00:06:39,065
and retired Police General Manuel Carillo.

103
00:06:39,148 --> 00:06:40,441
[in English] Until next time,

104
00:06:40,525 --> 00:06:43,402
this is Maya Mae Kalaw, <i>Inside the Truth</i>.

105
00:06:43,486 --> 00:06:46,489
[CBB music playing]

106
00:06:54,455 --> 00:06:56,082
- <i>My gosh, Mama Loi!</i>
- [Mama Loi] <i>Oh!</i>

107
00:06:56,165 --> 00:06:58,334
- <i>You won't believe this!</i>
- [Mama Loi] <i>What?</i>

108
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:00,920
<i>Did you guys watch it? Did you?</i>

109
00:07:01,003 --> 00:07:02,964
- [Mama Loi] <i>Watch what?</i>
- <i>My goodness!</i>

110
00:07:03,047 --> 00:07:07,885
<i>The latest episode</i>
<i>of Maya Mae Kalaw's</i> Inside the Truth.

111
00:07:07,969 --> 00:07:11,806
<i>Oh, yes! I saw it! It was unbelievable.</i>

112
00:07:11,889 --> 00:07:13,599
- <i>Seriously unbelievable!</i>
- <i>For real!</i>

113
00:07:13,683 --> 00:07:16,602
- <i>The revelations were intense!</i>
- <i>Yes.</i>

114
00:07:16,686 --> 00:07:21,315
<i>At first, we all thought</i>
<i>that terrorist couple</i>

115
00:07:21,399 --> 00:07:24,735
<i>hijacked the Japanese tour bus</i>

116
00:07:24,819 --> 00:07:27,613
<i>because they wanted to stop</i>
<i>that investment deal</i>

117
00:07:27,697 --> 00:07:29,157
<i>from going through.</i>

118
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:30,283
- <i>You've got a high voice.</i>
- <i>Yeah.</i>

119
00:07:30,366 --> 00:07:35,037
[high-pitched voice] <i>But when Maya Mae</i>
<i>started digging into the story…</i>

120
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:37,248
- [Mama Loi] <i>Oh my!</i>
- <i>tea started spilling.</i>

121
00:07:37,331 --> 00:07:39,500
[Mama Loi shrieks] <i>Exactly!</i>

122
00:07:39,584 --> 00:07:41,419
- <i>My voice is high too, right?</i>
- [Ogie] <i>Yeah!</i>

123
00:07:41,502 --> 00:07:43,754
- <i>And you know what's crazy?</i>
- [Ogie] <i>What?</i>

124
00:07:43,838 --> 00:07:47,008
<i>People who actually knew</i>
<i>those so-called terrorists</i>

125
00:07:47,091 --> 00:07:51,012
- <i>all said they were good people.</i>
- [Ogie] <i>Yes.</i>

126
00:07:51,095 --> 00:07:55,975
<i>They couldn't believe</i>
<i>they'd do something like that,</i>

127
00:07:56,058 --> 00:07:59,520
<i>especially since they had a little child</i>
<i>waiting for them at home.</i>

128
00:07:59,604 --> 00:08:02,231
- <i>That makes sense.</i>
- <i>Exactly.</i>

129
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:05,109
- <i>That's why I'm confused.</i>
- [Ogie] <i>Wow. You're confused?</i>

130
00:08:05,193 --> 00:08:09,572
<i>At first, I was furious</i>
<i>with those hostage-takers.</i>

131
00:08:09,655 --> 00:08:14,160
[Mrena] <i>But after learning</i>
<i>more about them…</i>

132
00:08:14,243 --> 00:08:16,204
- <i>Oh.</i>
- <i>now I feel sorry for them.</i>

133
00:08:16,287 --> 00:08:18,664
- <i>So you've had a change of heart.</i>
- <i>Yeah.</i>

134
00:08:18,748 --> 00:08:19,957
<i>Actually, that's just the way it is.</i>

135
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:24,670
<i>It's easy to judge somebody</i>
<i>when you don't know their story.</i>

136
00:08:24,754 --> 00:08:26,756
<i>But once you get to know them,</i>

137
00:08:26,839 --> 00:08:30,301
<i>you will be able to sympathize with them.</i>

138
00:08:30,384 --> 00:08:35,389
<i>So to you, Mrena,</i>
<i>and to everyone watching,</i>

139
00:08:35,473 --> 00:08:39,352
- <i>maybe ease up on the judgment.</i>
- <i>That's right.</i>

140
00:08:39,435 --> 00:08:44,774
<i>If we knew what other people</i>
<i>are going through,</i>

141
00:08:44,857 --> 00:08:48,778
<i>we might be giving them a hug</i>
<i>instead of judging them.</i>

142
00:08:48,861 --> 00:08:50,321
[Mama Loi] <i>Aww.</i>

143
00:08:50,404 --> 00:08:54,283
- <i>But, wait, Mother.</i>
- [Ogie] <i>What?</i>

144
00:08:54,367 --> 00:08:57,411
<i>Did you catch Agent Marcus's statement?</i>

145
00:08:57,495 --> 00:09:00,122
- <i>What is it? Oh, right!</i>
- <i>Yeah.</i>

146
00:09:00,206 --> 00:09:01,249
- <i>It was intriguing.</i>
- <i>Right?</i>

147
00:09:01,332 --> 00:09:04,669
<i>What do you think he meant when he said</i>

148
00:09:04,752 --> 00:09:08,714
<i>there was a deeper reason</i>
<i>behind the hostage-taking</i>

149
00:09:08,798 --> 00:09:14,470
<i>and that some powerful person</i>
<i>was pulling the strings?</i>

150
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:16,138
- [gasps]
- <i>My gosh.</i>

151
00:09:16,222 --> 00:09:19,225
<i>Agent Handsome is serving</i>
<i>a little blind item!</i>

152
00:09:19,308 --> 00:09:22,395
<i>You're so silly, Mrena!</i>

153
00:09:22,478 --> 00:09:26,941
<i>But seriously, I think</i>
<i>what Agent Marcus meant</i>

154
00:09:27,024 --> 00:09:29,735
<i>was that this case is far from over.</i>

155
00:09:29,819 --> 00:09:31,737
- <i>Oh.</i>
- <i>Yeah.</i>

156
00:09:31,821 --> 00:09:34,865
<i>They are still investigating it closely.</i>

157
00:09:34,949 --> 00:09:37,076
- <i>And that's exactly how it should be.</i>
- <i>Yeah.</i>

158
00:09:37,159 --> 00:09:39,120
<i>We shouldn't stop digging for the truth.</i>

159
00:09:39,203 --> 00:09:40,329
- <i>Yeah.</i>
- <i>Right?</i>

160
00:09:40,413 --> 00:09:43,708
<i>Until every question gets answered.</i>

161
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:46,836
<i>Correct. Let's remember.</i>

162
00:09:46,919 --> 00:09:50,381
<i>Asking questions isn't just our right.</i>

163
00:09:50,464 --> 00:09:53,384
- <i>That's right.</i>
- <i>It's our responsibility.</i>

164
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:54,468
[in English] <i>Correct.</i>

165
00:09:54,552 --> 00:09:56,262
- <i>But wait!</i>
- <i>Oh! What is it?</i>

166
00:09:56,345 --> 00:09:58,264
<i>The most important question…</i>

167
00:09:58,347 --> 00:09:59,974
- <i>What?</i>
- <i>Here it is.</i>

168
00:10:00,808 --> 00:10:02,977
- <i>Come on now.</i>
- <i>Mm-hmm.</i>

169
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:08,566
<i>When are they finally going to catch</i>
<i>the mastermind behind all this mess,</i>

170
00:10:08,649 --> 00:10:11,652
<i>so we can all have peace and quiet?</i>

171
00:10:11,736 --> 00:10:16,115
- [dramatic sting]
- [stirring music playing]

172
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:27,293
[Jamilah] Take your medicine
on time, okay?

173
00:10:27,376 --> 00:10:28,711
Thank you, sir.

174
00:10:32,882 --> 00:10:37,303
Doctor, here are the discharge
clearance papers and charts

175
00:10:37,386 --> 00:10:38,929
for the patient in Bed 14.

176
00:10:39,013 --> 00:10:40,931
You just need to sign it.

177
00:10:42,683 --> 00:10:44,268
Thank you, Jamilah.

178
00:10:46,729 --> 00:10:47,772
Doctor.

179
00:10:48,606 --> 00:10:51,651
Are you okay? Is something bothering you?

180
00:10:51,734 --> 00:10:55,863
[pensive music playing]

181
00:10:55,946 --> 00:10:57,740
Jamilah, what if…

182
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:01,410
What is it, Doctor?

183
00:11:03,412 --> 00:11:05,748
I don't know why, but…

184
00:11:08,417 --> 00:11:09,293
Allan…

185
00:11:11,921 --> 00:11:14,924
I have a feeling he's Gabriel,
my missing son.

186
00:11:15,007 --> 00:11:16,300
[tense music playing]

187
00:11:16,384 --> 00:11:17,968
What, Doctor?

188
00:11:19,345 --> 00:11:21,222
How could that be possible?

189
00:11:22,223 --> 00:11:24,350
I don't know why, but…

190
00:11:25,393 --> 00:11:28,354
whenever I'm with Allan,
I feel something different.

191
00:11:31,023 --> 00:11:33,401
I feel like there's
a connection between us.

192
00:11:33,984 --> 00:11:37,738
The way he moves… his eyes…

193
00:11:39,490 --> 00:11:41,826
Maybe I'm going crazy, but…

194
00:11:41,909 --> 00:11:45,204
[pensive music playing]

195
00:11:45,287 --> 00:11:49,375
Maybe I'm just hoping again
that my son is still alive.

196
00:11:52,253 --> 00:11:53,712
I have to…

197
00:11:54,588 --> 00:11:56,590
I have to try.

198
00:11:57,258 --> 00:11:59,093
I need answers.

199
00:12:01,053 --> 00:12:02,680
[PA announcement] <i>Dr. Teresa Reyes.</i>

200
00:12:02,763 --> 00:12:05,766
[in English] <i>Please proceed</i>
<i>to Trauma Room 3 immediately.</i>

201
00:12:05,850 --> 00:12:09,019
[in English] <i>Dr. Teresa Reyes,</i>
<i>to Trauma Room 3, please.</i>

202
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:11,272
- [in English] Excuse me.
- Okay.

203
00:12:28,289 --> 00:12:30,124
[Jamilah] <i>If Doctor Teresa does that,</i>

204
00:12:30,624 --> 00:12:34,044
<i>she'll discover</i>
<i>Major Espina's true identity!</i>

205
00:12:36,213 --> 00:12:37,506
<i>That can't happen.</i>

206
00:12:38,007 --> 00:12:40,342
<i>Jalil's plan will be ruined.</i>

207
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:44,096
[dramatic sting]

208
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:46,891
[Usman] My mother said
the child disappeared

209
00:12:46,974 --> 00:12:49,685
a few days before the bus hostage crisis.

210
00:12:50,936 --> 00:12:52,938
The couple even cried to her

211
00:12:53,022 --> 00:12:55,733
because they couldn't find
their daughter, Jennie.

212
00:12:56,609 --> 00:12:58,569
The child was used to blackmail them.

213
00:13:00,821 --> 00:13:03,115
To force them into hijacking the bus.

214
00:13:03,824 --> 00:13:04,950
But why?

215
00:13:05,659 --> 00:13:07,661
Because they were part of the plan.

216
00:13:08,162 --> 00:13:11,582
They were never meant
to make it out alive.

217
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:14,251
But the one who suffered
the most is the child.

218
00:13:15,377 --> 00:13:16,962
She's an orphan now.

219
00:13:17,546 --> 00:13:21,008
And in everyone's eyes,
her parents are criminals.

220
00:13:23,093 --> 00:13:24,220
[in English] Goddammit!

221
00:13:25,137 --> 00:13:27,014
We need to stop

222
00:13:27,097 --> 00:13:30,392
all of General Carillo's evil schemes.

223
00:13:30,476 --> 00:13:32,853
[tense music playing]

224
00:13:33,521 --> 00:13:37,149
But, sir… Getting close to General Carillo
won't be easy.

225
00:13:38,359 --> 00:13:39,443
He's quick to sense
when something's wrong.

226
00:13:41,570 --> 00:13:43,822
I watched Maya Mae Kalaw's documentary.

227
00:13:44,615 --> 00:13:46,867
Apparently, Mustapha and General Carillo

228
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:48,744
are going to face each other
in a live interview.

229
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:53,123
That's your chance.

230
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:56,085
After that,

231
00:13:56,585 --> 00:14:00,965
they'll definitely move forward
with all their evil plans.

232
00:14:01,048 --> 00:14:05,094
[dramatic sting]

233
00:14:20,359 --> 00:14:24,864
[pensive music playing]

234
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:49,722
[suspenseful music playing]

235
00:15:07,281 --> 00:15:11,285
[dramatic sting]

236
00:15:19,793 --> 00:15:22,046
[Jamilah] <i>I'm sorry, Doctor,</i>

237
00:15:22,588 --> 00:15:25,341
<i>but I have to protect Jalil.</i>

238
00:15:26,926 --> 00:15:30,971
[music intensifies]

239
00:15:54,912 --> 00:16:00,000
Nice work. We're slowly winning them over.

240
00:16:01,418 --> 00:16:05,422
General, Marcus Reyes is here
asking for you, sir.

241
00:16:05,506 --> 00:16:07,508
[uneasy music playing]

242
00:16:07,591 --> 00:16:08,550
Send him in.

243
00:16:08,634 --> 00:16:09,510
Yes, sir.

244
00:16:13,263 --> 00:16:14,348
[door clicks open]

245
00:16:16,767 --> 00:16:18,560
- General.
- Sir.

246
00:16:19,061 --> 00:16:22,439
Young man… What are you doing here?

247
00:16:23,107 --> 00:16:28,070
Sir, Lara hasn't checked in
at HQ for days now.

248
00:16:28,153 --> 00:16:29,947
We can't reach her.

249
00:16:30,531 --> 00:16:32,533
We're really concerned about her.

250
00:16:34,159 --> 00:16:37,246
Lara's grown up now.
She can handle herself.

251
00:16:37,329 --> 00:16:42,626
I don't always know where she is
or who she's with.

252
00:16:44,586 --> 00:16:45,671
I understand, sir.

253
00:16:45,754 --> 00:16:49,049
Just hoping you might know

254
00:16:49,133 --> 00:16:51,760
where she is or when she might be back.

255
00:16:51,844 --> 00:16:53,387
[in English] Well, I don't.

256
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:55,180
But don't worry.

257
00:16:55,264 --> 00:16:57,683
I'll have Raquel give her a call.

258
00:16:57,766 --> 00:17:01,270
[in English] I'm sure
there's nothing to worry about.

259
00:17:01,979 --> 00:17:03,105
Sir…

260
00:17:04,189 --> 00:17:08,277
Buster, a guy
who was always with Lara at HQ,

261
00:17:09,653 --> 00:17:13,365
he said Lara vanished
right after the explosion.

262
00:17:14,199 --> 00:17:15,743
And we haven't been able
to find her since either.

263
00:17:15,826 --> 00:17:18,704
Did you happen to speak with Lara

264
00:17:18,787 --> 00:17:20,873
before or after the blast?

265
00:17:20,956 --> 00:17:23,834
[pensive music playing]

266
00:17:23,917 --> 00:17:25,794
[in English] Is this what I think it is?

267
00:17:25,878 --> 00:17:31,800
[in English] At exactly
1:45 p.m. tomorrow,

268
00:17:31,884 --> 00:17:35,804
you will have to press that button.

269
00:17:36,513 --> 00:17:37,347
Why me?

270
00:17:38,724 --> 00:17:40,309
[in English] Because…

271
00:17:41,226 --> 00:17:45,731
I want to know if you

272
00:17:47,107 --> 00:17:52,362
are still the daughter that I raised.

273
00:17:52,446 --> 00:17:53,906
[exhales softly]

274
00:17:53,989 --> 00:17:58,368
[brooding music playing]

275
00:18:04,917 --> 00:18:06,126
No.

276
00:18:14,051 --> 00:18:15,135
Alright, sir.

277
00:18:16,512 --> 00:18:17,846
Thank you for your time.

278
00:18:20,182 --> 00:18:24,603
[suspenseful music playing]

279
00:18:36,698 --> 00:18:39,993
[phone vibrating]

280
00:18:40,619 --> 00:18:44,081
[loud huff]

281
00:18:48,961 --> 00:18:49,920
General.

282
00:18:50,629 --> 00:18:53,298
Felix. Tell me the truth.

283
00:18:53,382 --> 00:18:55,759
Were you the one
who pressed the detonator?

284
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:00,180
[sighs]

285
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:03,684
‪[sighs]

286
00:19:04,810 --> 00:19:06,979
[in English] Felix, answer me!

287
00:19:12,317 --> 00:19:13,527
[in English] Yes, General.

288
00:19:15,362 --> 00:19:16,488
It was me.

289
00:19:16,572 --> 00:19:19,700
- [breathes heavily, screams]
- [phone clatters]

290
00:19:19,783 --> 00:19:23,912
[music intensifies]

291
00:19:23,996 --> 00:19:27,916
- [Manuel sobs]
- [glass breaks]

292
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:31,587
[screaming]

293
00:19:31,670 --> 00:19:36,592
- [breathing heavily]
- [thuds]

294
00:19:40,429 --> 00:19:43,098
[sobs]

295
00:19:43,182 --> 00:19:44,016
‪[dramatic sting]

296
00:19:47,769 --> 00:19:50,063
[somber music playing]

297
00:19:50,147 --> 00:19:53,233
[sighs deeply]

298
00:19:53,317 --> 00:19:54,610
Cuchy…

299
00:19:55,110 --> 00:19:57,487
[sighs deeply]

300
00:19:58,071 --> 00:20:00,282
What do you think?

301
00:20:00,365 --> 00:20:03,827
[ominous music playing]

302
00:20:03,911 --> 00:20:06,330
Are we really going to lose…

303
00:20:08,540 --> 00:20:09,541
Madam?

304
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:25,515
[Lara breathing in panic]

305
00:20:25,599 --> 00:20:27,517
Madam! Madam!

306
00:20:27,601 --> 00:20:29,186
What's going on with you?

307
00:20:29,269 --> 00:20:30,479
[sobs]

308
00:20:40,364 --> 00:20:41,531
[inhales sharply]

309
00:20:42,658 --> 00:20:45,160
[groans]

310
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:47,120
[Manuel] <i>I love this kid.</i>

311
00:20:48,413 --> 00:20:52,751
So, make sure she doesn't get hurt.

312
00:20:53,752 --> 00:20:57,965
The moment she becomes a hindrance

313
00:20:58,632 --> 00:21:00,634
to our plans…

314
00:21:00,717 --> 00:21:04,680
[dramatic sting]

315
00:21:06,932 --> 00:21:08,267
[screams]

316
00:21:11,061 --> 00:21:11,979
[muffled grunt]

317
00:21:14,231 --> 00:21:15,190
[muffled grunt]

318
00:21:16,275 --> 00:21:18,068
[breathing heavily]

319
00:21:18,777 --> 00:21:19,820
Lara…

320
00:21:20,737 --> 00:21:21,738
Lara…

321
00:21:23,282 --> 00:21:25,867
[exhales] What exactly are you planning?

322
00:21:26,368 --> 00:21:27,452
[sniffles]

323
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:30,205
Where have you gone?

324
00:21:30,998 --> 00:21:32,374
[sniffles]

325
00:21:32,457 --> 00:21:33,500
[chuckles] Lara…

326
00:21:34,668 --> 00:21:36,920
[giggles]

327
00:21:37,004 --> 00:21:38,046
Don't…

328
00:21:38,797 --> 00:21:40,007
[sniffles]

329
00:21:40,674 --> 00:21:43,385
Don't make a mistake, Lara.

330
00:21:44,011 --> 00:21:44,845
‪[sniffles]

331
00:21:46,722 --> 00:21:48,890
[sighs]

332
00:21:48,974 --> 00:21:50,809
I don't want to kill you.

333
00:21:53,937 --> 00:21:56,023
I don't want to kill you, Lara.

334
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:02,279
But…

335
00:22:04,406 --> 00:22:06,116
just like I said…

336
00:22:11,079 --> 00:22:12,998
I shall do what General says.

337
00:22:14,875 --> 00:22:19,254
[crying softly]

338
00:22:19,338 --> 00:22:23,383
[music intensifies]

339
00:22:30,599 --> 00:22:31,850
[gasps]

340
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:34,519
Who are you? What are you doing?

341
00:22:34,603 --> 00:22:35,645
Why are you here?

342
00:22:36,313 --> 00:22:37,564
[grunts]

343
00:22:50,911 --> 00:22:53,080
[Marcus] <i>Why did you disappear, Lara?</i>

344
00:22:53,163 --> 00:22:54,873
<i>Did you make the bus explode?</i>

345
00:22:55,832 --> 00:23:01,088
[Ahmad] <i>Lara is the weakest link</i>
<i>in Carillo's group.</i>

346
00:23:01,171 --> 00:23:02,422
You have to find her.

347
00:23:02,506 --> 00:23:04,382
Her life is in danger.

348
00:23:05,258 --> 00:23:08,428
Who are you?
Why are you doing this? [choking]

349
00:23:09,262 --> 00:23:11,807
I hope my hunch is wrong.

350
00:23:12,808 --> 00:23:15,852
[Lara] <i>Were you involved</i>
<i>in my parents' death?</i>

351
00:23:15,936 --> 00:23:17,771
<i>I'll make you pay.</i>

352
00:23:18,647 --> 00:23:20,816
What happened to you, Agent Angeles?

353
00:23:20,899 --> 00:23:23,443
[Espina] <i>Is Sir Mustapha</i>
<i>telling the truth?</i>

354
00:23:23,527 --> 00:23:25,654
Is your life really in danger?

355
00:23:25,737 --> 00:23:27,614
Tell me the truth!

356
00:23:27,697 --> 00:23:29,866
I'm your only ally.

357
00:23:29,950 --> 00:23:32,452
Answer my question! Is it true?
